description.plain:
City Girls, which is comprised of JT and Yung Miami, is a Miami-based rap duo—most notably recognized and struck a major come-up in 2018, as they released their November smash hit, “Act Up,” and appeared in Drake’s June viral hit, “In My Feelings.”

Their debut single, “Fuck Dat Nigga,” earned a placement on Quality Control’s compilation album Control The Streets Vol 1 in 2017—the City Girls signed a contract with Quality Control to be under their record label soon after.

On May 11, 2018, the duo released their debut mixtape PERIOD, which lead up to the release of their debut album Girl Code on November 16, 2018. Two years later, they dropped a 2020 studio album titled City On Lock—garnering major features such as Lil Baby, Lil Durk, and Doja Cat.

songs.title: Act Up

description.plain:
On this Girl Code standout, JT and Yung Miami rap how someone shouldn’t “Act Up” with them, otherwise there may be consequences.

Since its release, the song has gained notoriety, mostly due to the song’s social media challenge, the #ActUpChallenge. Participants of the challenge post video clips of themselves drinking, smoking, twerking and may also post pictures of their exes and former friends.

In an April 2019 interview, Lil Yachty, who’s credited as a co-writer on the song, said he wrote all of it except for JT’s final verse.

description.plain:
“Twerk” is City Girls' ode to booty-shaking and female empowerment. It features fast-paced flows and booming 808s, accompanied by a Choppa sample from 2002’s “Choppa Style.” The original contained no features, but Cardi B contributed a verse to the radio edit and subsequent music video.

Motown Records announced the single via Twitter on November 8, 2018:

https://twitter.com/motown/status/1060762111041781760
